It would seem that President Cyril Ramaphosa does not have a plan regarding the expropriation of land. The government has failed for more than 24 years to redress the land issue. MPs voted in favour of a motion to begin the process to amend Section 25 of the Constitution to allow land expropriation without compensation. The government must wait now for the Constitutional Review Committee to make the amendment. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  